.TH "TEMPORAL.ZONEDDATETIME.OFFSET" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.offset \- Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.offset
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]offset\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instances returns a string
representing the offset used to interpret the internal instant, in the
form \f[CR]±HH:mm\f[R] (or \f[CR]±HH:mm:ss.sssssssss\f[R] with as much
subminute precision as necessary).
This offset is guaranteed to be valid for the given instant and time
zone at construction time.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]offset\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
Use the \f[CR]with()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object with the desired new value
(usually also changing the date/time), or use the
\f[CR]withTimeZone()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object in another time zone.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using offset
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(
  \(dq2021\-07\-01T12:00:00\-07:00[America/Los_Angeles]\(dq,
);
console.log(dt.offset); \f[I]// \(dq\-07:00\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] dt2 = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T12:00:00\-07[\-07]\(dq);
console.log(dt2.offset); \f[I]// \(dq\-07:00\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] dt3 = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(
  \(dq1900\-01\-01T00:00:00+00:09:21[Europe/Paris]\(dq,
);
console.log(dt3.offset); \f[I]// \(dq+00:09:21\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] dt4 = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T12:00:00Z[Asia/Shanghai]\(dq);
console.log(dt4.offset); \f[I]// \(dq+08:00\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Changing offset
If the local time happens to have two valid offsets, such as within a
DST transition, you can change the offset without changing anything
else:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] zdt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(
  \(dq2024\-11\-03T01:05:00\-04:00[America/New_York]\(dq,
);
\f[B]const\f[R] newZDT = zdt.with({ offset: \(dq\-05:00\(dq });
console.log(newZDT.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2024\-11\-03T01:05:00\-05:00[America/New_York]\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
